+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01S3eiupvwivyAbo3VEbXFTp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I'll add the search and suggest routes to routes.ts. The key considerations from the tests:\n\n1. `GET /notes/search?q=<query>` - FTS5 search, BM25 ranked, `<mark>` snippets, pagination (page/perPage), returns `{results, total, page, perPage}`\n2. `GET /notes/search/suggest?q=<prefix>` - up to 5 matching titles\n3. Both return 400 if `q` is missing or empty\n4. Special characters must not crash (need to handle FTS5 syntax errors)\n\nNote: The suggest endpoint needs to match prefix - looking at test 14, it matches \"getting\" in title. The test uses `?q=learn` and expects matches. I'll use FTS5 prefix queries (`term*`) for suggest.\n\nAlso note test 4: ranks should be in ascending order (lower rank = more relevant). FTS5 BM25 returns negative values where more negative = more relevant, so ascending order means most relevant first."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":274,"cache_read_input_tokens":41009,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":274},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cb76acaf-9e2e-4d93-96b5-34879fe91f5f","uuid":"9665b2bf-de88-4d58-9da6-57aeb719ff0d"}
